    {
      "id": "73",
      "name": "Lore",
      "components": [
        {
          "component_id": "customize",
          "data": {
            "data": {
              "parsed_content": [
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 255, 255)"
                      ],
                      "text": "Moonchase Festival",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "level": 1,
                  "type": "heading"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "alignment": "left",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/06/14/237301566/2e14e4aeb0e70b758692b96a7cecbaa6_568972349750487774.png"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "The Moonchase Festival is one of Liyue's age-old traditions, a grand celebration marking the arrival of the fall by moonlight. In ancient times, this festival was believed to be when Adepti sought the \"Way,\" but at present, it is a time for joy and relaxation. Moonchase originally served as a rite exclusive to the Adepti. According to legend, in their pursuit of the Adeptal path, Adepti traversed mountains and rivers, indulging in a variety of gourmet dishes to find solace for their hearts. Later generations referred to their journey as the \"Trail of Delicacies.\"",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "alignment": "right",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/06/14/237301566/99d363bf24aefe0935064ebb44b197d6_1024955543672486481.png"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Various festivals bearing the Moonchase name sprouted among the people of Liyue as they sought to emulate the original rite. During moonlit nights, people gathered for joyful reunions, featuring exquisite food, wines, and teas. Rex Lapis unified these diverse celebrations under Moonchase, honoring an old friend, the Stove God. Rex Lapis, acknowledging his friend's contributions to Liyue, sought to immortalize his friend’s memory. This collective vow to the moon symbolized joyful solidarity, a commemoration of the past, and reflection on the present, which is the essence of the Moonchase Festival. Each year, the Moonchase Festival adopts a unique theme, usually chosen by the Qixing. One folktale claimed that the ancients found the Stove God's shrine, but there was no statue — only a huge, smooth slab of stone.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "alignment": "left",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/06/14/237301566/2f19fd579241cb39e2ce8e1f430f8d3a_3058468486224952550.png"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "The Adeptus Streetward Rambler, revealed that the Stove God was her close friend, now lost to memory and the world. Although the Stove God passed, a pact was made to await his return in a new form once the land became fertile again. Marchosius was once the Patron God of the Soil, all the wisdom and power he had, he has since surrendered to the soil itself to prevent the kinds of trials and tribulations that a land can face, such as droughts, floods, torrential rain, hurricanes, earthquakes, tsunamis, fires, and plagues. He once walked over the barren plains with the people until arriving at last at the harbor. He joined humans in building their dwellings and lighting the stoves. It was his hand that lit the very first street lamp of Liyue and brought the aroma of cooked food into every household in the land. Mortals no longer remember him, but back in the age when they did, he was the closest of all the Adepti to the common folk.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 215, 128)"
                      ],
                      "text": "Related Entries:",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
