    {
      "id": "95",
      "name": "Event",
      "components": [
        {
          "component_id": "customize",
          "data": {
            "data": {
              "parsed_content": [
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 255, 255)"
                      ],
                      "text": "Moonlight Merriment",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "level": 1,
                  "type": "heading"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "alignment": "left",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/06/13/178140791/6eae5d30e791e9690f84ed2d8f8a1f74_3306298455782059670.png"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Moonchase Festival falls during the season when many cooking ingredients are ripe, hence it is a fitting time to enjoy the finest of foods. The people of Liyue indulge in their favorite foods, share moments with friends and family, and revel in the beauty of the moon and flowers. The Traveler’s first Moonchase Festival consisted of the theme \"Feast of the Bounteous Land\" which included a cooking competition called \"Masterful Chefs,\" as chosen by the Liyue Qixing. Xiangling, a talented and passionate young chef from Liyue, sought inspiration for a cooking competition and recruited the Traveler and Paimon to gather ideas. They encountered various people and gained different perspectives of the \"perfect dish.\" Xiangling advanced in the Masterful Chefs competition after presenting three new test dishes: Chicken Foo Yung, Come and Get It, and Crystal Shrimp. Feedback from the people of Liyue prompted her to make adjustments for the finals, where she presented Jueyun Chili Chicken, Triple-Layered Consommé, and Crystal Shrimp, and ultimately won the competition against Smiley Yanxiao, who was then the second finalist.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "alignment": "right",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/06/14/237301566/9ed83fa2d6bcada9bf8363303f7d7797_3220316689765694858.jpg"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "All throughout their preparation for the cooking tournament, the group had searched for information about the Stove God as they thought there was a connection between a stone found by a fisherman and the Stove God. They gathered information from various sources, including Granny Ruoxin in Qingce Village, Xingqiu's book collection, and an ancient tome kept by Smiley Yanxiao at Wangshu Inn. After the cooking competition, the group searched for Keqing, the Yuheng of the Liyue Qixing, to share Chili-Mince Cornbread Buns. Keqing shared with the group that the recipe was an ancient dish from her grandfather's notes about the Stove God.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "alignment": "left",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/06/13/178140791/d17b41f4cb589879c7566a66ffbd8f76_6773908112068553721.png"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Xiangling was reminded that she made this dish on the day she first met Guoba in a cave in the mountains. She ducked inside to get out of the rain and put the Cornbread Buns on an offering table she saw there. She fell asleep, and when she woke up, Guoba had eaten every last one. Guoba has followed her around ever since. Then suddenly, the stone cracked and revealed Guoba to be the Stove God, Marchosius. Madame Ping explained that Marchosius had always been a deity with great affection for the people, and acted in response to their desires. Passion alone will not suffice to reawaken Marchosius from his deep slumber, but when Keqing ate Chili-Mince Cornbread Buns, a traditional folk-food snack, a deeply held desire was fulfilled. The enormous power unleashed by the fulfillment of this desire resonated with Marchosius’s statue and caused it to manifest once more the form it took in the past. Guoba may have lost many of his former faculties, but he is now as carefree as can be, without a single worry in the whole world. Those with a mind and with knowledge will certainly be troubled by all manner of things. His carefree demeanor today is a testament to the fact that he is at rest.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 215, 128)"
                      ],
                      "text": "Related Entries:",
                      "type": "text"
